devdoc.details: Implement main contract for Insurance. contract between insurance and farmers is materialized in here

InsuranceActivated(uint16,bytes32,bytes3.details: Emitted when a `contract` is activated by an `insurer` for a given `season` + `region` + `farmID`

InsuranceClosed(uint16,bytes32,bytes32,u.details: Emitted when a `contract` is closed without any compensation

InsuranceCompensated(uint16,bytes32,byte.details: Emitted when a `contract` is closed with any compensation

InsuranceRequested(uint16,bytes32,bytes3.details: Emitted when a `contract` is submitted by an `farmer` for a given `season` + `region` + `farmID`

InsuranceValidated(uint16,bytes32,bytes3.details: Emitted when a `contract` is validated by a `government` for a given `season` + `region` + `farmID`

WithdrawInsurer(address,uint256,uint256).details: Emitted when an `insurer` withdraws `amount` from the contract. remaining contract balance is `balance`

params.farmID: unique ID of a farm  Emits a {InsuranceActivated} event. Requirements: - Contract is active (circuit-breaker) - Can only be called by insurer - Check must exist - Season must be open - contract must be in VALIDATED state - Must be enough eth staked within the contract after the operation

constructor.details: Initialize `rules` for compensation. Also setup `gatekeeer` and `oracleFacade`

params._key: keecak combination of season, region & farmID

returns.size: number of HA of a farmer (minimum: 1 HA)

params._key: keecak combination of season, region & farmID

returns.severity: Drought severity fetched from oracleFacade when the contract is closed
returns.totalStaked: eth that were taked in this contract

returns.size: number of HA of a farmer (minimum: 1 HA)

returns.severity: Drought severity when the contract is closed
returns.totalStaked: eth that were taked in this contract

getEscrow().details: retrieve the address of the escrow contract

getGateKeeper().details: retrieve the address of the gateKeeper contract

getNumberClosedContracts(uint16,bytes32).details: get number of closed contracts for a given season and region

getNumberClosedContractsByKey(bytes32).details: get number of closed contracts for a given key

getNumberOpenContracts(uint16,bytes32).details: get number of open contracts for a given season and region

getNumberOpenContractsByKey(bytes32).details: get number of open contracts for a given key

minimumAmount().details: calculate at anytime the minimum liquidity that must be locked within the contract

returns._0: ammount Basically , always enough money to pay keepers and compensation in worst case scenarios

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

process(uint16,bytes32).details: process an insurance file. triggered by a `keeper`as a combination of `season`,`region` can have several open insurances files, a keeper will have to loop over this function until there are no more open insurances files. looping is done offchain rather than onchain in order to avoid any out of gas exception

params.region: region ID  Emits a {InsuranceClosed} event in case an insurance file has been closed without any compensation (e.g.: Drought severity <= D1) or returned back becase government has not staked 1/2 of the premium  Emits a {InsuranceCompensated} event in case an insurance file has been processed with compensation (e.g.: Drought severity >= D2) Requirements: - Contract is active (circuit-breaker) - Can only be called by keeper - Check contract must exist - Season must be closed - Must be open contracts to process - Must be enough eth staked within the contract

register(uint16,bytes32,bytes32,uint256).details: submission of an insurance request by a farmer

params.size: number of HA of a farmer (minimum: 1 HA)

returns._0: key key of the contract  Emits a {InsuranceRequested} event. Requirements: - contract is Active (circuit-breaker) - Can only be called by farmer - Check non duplicate - Seasonmust be open - Sender must pay for premium - Must be enough eth staked within the contract

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setGateKeeper(address).details: Allow to change dynamically access control contract (GateKeeper)

params._gateKeeper: gateKeeper address Requirements: - only owner can change the reference of GateKeeper - ensure that it impelments the right interface

switchContractOff().details: If the contract is active then stop it and emit a {ContractOff} event. Requirements: - the caller must be root admin.

switchContractOn().details: If the contract is stopped then active it and emit a {ContractOn} event. Requirements: - the caller must be root admin.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

validate(uint16,bytes32,bytes32).details: validate a request done by a farmer

params.farmID: unique ID of a farm  Emits a {InsuranceValidated} event. Requirements: - Contract is active (circuit-breaker) - Can only be called by government - Check contract must exist - Season must be open - Sender must pay for premium - Must be enough eth staked within the contract

withdraw().details: Withdraw accumulated balance for a payee Requirements: - msg.sender must have enough balance in the escrow

withdrawInsurer(uint256).details: an insurer can withdraw any excess of liquidity

params.amount: to be withdrawed  Emits a {WithdrawInsurer} event. Requirements: - Can only be called by insurer - Check non duplicate - Must be enough eth staked within the contract after operation

withdrawableInsurer().details: check anytime amount that can be withdrawed by insurer

HALF_PERMIUM_PER_HA.details: used for calculation (farmer must stake half of premium. Same for government)

closedContracts.details: contracts that have already been closed by season,region

contracts.details: a contract is a unique combination between season,region,farmID

openContracts.details: contracts that must be treated by season,region

oracleFacade.details: OracleFacade used to get the status of a season(open/closed) and Severity for a given season + region

rules.details: rules to calculate the compensation D1 gives 0.5 times the premium D2 gives 1 times the premium D3 gives 2 times the premium D4 gives 2.5 times the premium

totalOpenContracts.details: needed to track amount to be paid for keepers

totalOpenSize.details: needed to track worst case scenario -> must have at anytime money to pay for severity/D4 : 2.5*PERMIUM_PER_HA*totalsize
